It is not known if Fernández will continue to be politically active after her term ends, even without the support of her husband.
If so, it needs the support of the middle class, which has had enough of Kirchnerism for the most part.
When the Argentines return from their summer vacation in March, the wave of sympathy shown to them will have died away.
If she wants to win another election, she needs to decide whether she wants to quietly overturn many of her husband's political decisions.
